dule-mode compilation pipeline | ~347 | 🛠️ 8,841 |\\n\\n**scripts/run-ocaml.sh**\\n| ID | Time | T | Title | Read | Work |\\n|----|------|---|-------|------|------|\\n| #36367 | 11:50 AM | ✅ | Updated runner scripts to use pv24t and single-module .p24 files | ~375 | 🛠️ 5,983 |\\n\\n**General**\\n| ID | Time | T | Title | Read | Work |\\n|----|------|---|-------|------|------|\\n| #36370 | 11:51 AM | ✅ | Rebuild successful with 37 of 65 regression tests passing | ~339 | 🛠️ 1,270 |\\n\\n**work/reg-rs/canonical_list_filter.out**\\n| ID | Time | T | Title | Read | Work |\\n|----|------|---|-------|------|------|\\n| #36371 | 11:55 AM | 🔵 | Regression test failures due to list pretty-printing removing semicolons | ~360 | 🔍 643 |\\n\\n**General**\\n| ID | Time | T | Title | Read | Work |\\n|----|------|---|-------|------|------|\\n| #36372 | 11:56 AM | 🔵 | List output semicolons missing only in cor24-run, work correctly in pv24t | ~339 | 🔍 680 |\\n| #36373 | 12:01 PM | 🔵 | Relocated .p24m via p24-load fixes cor24-run semicolon bug | ~360 | 🔍 608 |\\n\\n**scripts/build.sh**\\n| ID | Time | T | Title | Read | Work |\\n|----|------|---|-------|------|------|\\n| #36374 | \\\" | 🔴 | Added p24-load relocation step to build pipeline for cor24-run compatibility | ~353 | 🛠️ 3,486 |\\n\\n**scripts/run-ocaml.sh**\\n| ID | Time | T | Title | Read | Work |\\n|----|------|---|-------|------|------|\\n| #36375 | \\\" | 🔴 | Updated run-ocaml.sh to use relocated ocaml.p24m for correct cor24-run output | ~335 | 🛠️ 5,759 |\\n\\n**General**\\n| ID | Time | T | Title | Read | Work |\\n|----|------|---|-------|------|------|\\n| #36376 | 12:03 PM | 🔴 | Regression tests improved from 37 to 61 passing after p24-load fix | ~378 | 🛠️ 1,133 |\\n\\n**#S4670** Document agentrail workflow requirements (tracking, committing, pushing) and discuss commit/push conventions (Apr 17 at 12:10 PM)\\n\\n**src/ocaml.pas**\\n| ID | Time | T | Title | Read | Work |\\n|----|------|---|-------|------|------|\\n| #36377 | 12:10 PM | 🔵 | int_of_string implementation located in OCaml interpreter | ~260 | 🔍 1,231 |\\n| #36378 | 12:15 PM | 🔵 | Empty string handling identified as root cause of REPL input bug | ~292 | 🔍 973 |\\n| #36380 | 12:18 PM | 🔵 | Builtin function dispatch mechanism and read_line implementation found | ~316 | 🔍 1,186 |\\n| #36383 | 12:23 PM | ✅ | Added exit builtin global variables to OCaml interpreter | ~250 | 🛠️ 36,208 |\\n| #36384 | 12:24 PM | ✅ | Registered exit builtin name in name pool | ~304 | 🛠️ 37,580 |\\n| #36385 | \\\" | ✅ | Added exit builtin identifier resolution in evaluator | ~308 | 🛠️ 37,399 |\\n| #36391 | 12:38 PM | 🟣 | Implemented exit builtin function to terminate OCaml REPL | ~351 | 🛠️ 37,566 |\\n\\n**#S4673** Push changes to sw-cor24-pcode and sw-cor24-ocaml repositories with pv24t enhancements and demo improvements (Apr 17 at 1:00 PM)\\n\\n**CLAUDE.md**\\n| ID | Time | T | Title | Read | Work |\\n|----|------|---|-------|------|------|\\n\\n**#36403** 1:01 PM ✅ **Updated agentrail workflow to require pushing commits**\\n\\nThe agentrail step protocol in CLAUDE.md has been updated to require pushing commits immediately after creation. Section 4 now titled \\\"COMMIT AND PUSH\\\" includes git push in the workflow commands and adds explicit guidance that work existing only locally can be lost. The new requirement extends to sibling repositories, mandating that agents commit and push in every touched repo before proceeding, rather than deferring pushes to the end of a session. This establishes a stricter workflow discipline ensuring all work is immediately backed up to remote repositories.\\n\\nRead: ~289, Work: 🛠️ 6,110\\n\\n**../sw-cor24-pcode/tracer/src/lib.rs**\\n| ID | Time | T | Title | Read | Work |\\n|----|------|---|-------|------|------|\\n\\n**#36404** \\\" 🔵 **Pcode VM arena sizes increased for larger programs**\\n\\nThe pcode VM in sw-cor24-pcode has uncommitted arena size expansions to support larger programs. Call and eval stacks grew 16x (256 to 4096 words each), while heap memory expanded 256x (256 to 65536 words). These changes address memory constraints that would prevent running more complex Pascal programs in the VM. The repository's recent commit history shows related VM hardening work including stack overflow detection and data reference relocation fixes.\\n\\nRead: ~238, Work: 🔍 1,613\\n\\n**../sw-cor24-pcode/tracer/src/lib.rs**\\n| ID | Time | T | Title | Read | Work |\\n|----|------|---|-------|------|------|\\n\\n**#36408** 1:20 PM 🔴 **Fixed pcode VM arena sizes to prevent OOM in tree-walk interpreters**\\n\\nThe pcode VM's arena sizes were too small for OCaml-style tree-walk evaluators that allocate PVal and PEnv structures during execution. With only 768 bytes of heap, the memory allocator began returning duplicate addresses after a few allocations, causing live closures and environments to be overwritten. This manifested as EVAL ERROR failures in recursive functions like factorial at depth 3. The fix expands heap memory 256x to 65536 words (~192KB) and stack memories 16x to 4096 words each, providing sufficient space for interpreter data structures while remaining within the embedded system's memory constraints. This enables sw-cor24-ocaml programs to run successfully on the pv24t VM target.\\n\\nRead: ~347, Work: 🛠️ 1,381\\n\\n**General**\\n| ID | Time | T | Title | Read | Work |\\n|----|------|---|-------|------|------|\\n\\n**#36410** 1:23 PM ⚖️ **Repository modification policy established**\\n\\nA strict repository modification policy was established after unauthorized changes were made to an external repository. The workflow now requires that any fixes or changes needed in other repositories must be requested through proper channels rather than being implemented directly. This includes both forward changes and reversions. The policy ensures proper ownership boundaries and prevents uncoordinated modifications across repository boundaries.\\n\\nRead: ~227, Work: ⚖️ 2,930\\n\\n**#S4679** Establish git branching strategy (dev and feature branches) and set project scope boundaries for sw-cor24-ocaml (Apr 17 at 5:45 PM)\\n\\n**General**\\n| ID | Time | T | Title | Read | Work |\\n|----|------|---|-------|------|------|\\n\\n**#36446** 5:45 PM ✅ **Created and pushed dev branch from main**\\n\\nA new development branch 'dev' was created from the main branch to serve as an intermediate layer in the branching strategy. The branch was immediately pushed to the remote repository with upstream tracking configured, establishing it as the base for future feature branches. At creation time, dev is identical to main since no changes have been made yet.\\n\\nRead: ~171, Work: 🛠️ 896\\n\\n\\nAccess 280k tokens of past research & decisions for just 16,157t. Use MCP search tools to access memories by ID.\"}}\n","stderr":"","exitCode":0,"command":"node \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/bun-runner.js\" \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/worker-service.cjs\" hook claude-code context","durationMs":386},"type":"attachment","uuid":"5c6da12e-bcb9-4908-97f3-a0d9b3de32f4","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:19:11.756Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/mike/github/sw-embed/sw-cor24-ocaml","sessionId":"e5aefad8-ffa8-4fca-baff-df2b7b63be1b","version":"2.1.116","gitBranch":"feat/wip"}
