{"parentUuid":"d6757df2-59df-4f0f-abee-87af2ac94cc5","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"b5255dbd-971a-431a-870f-016efd538b87","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Note web agent is blocked: TRAP 2 reproduces in the CLI with the same input sequence (look, take, inventory, n, s, take). This is an upstream OCaml interpreter\n  bug — nothing the web UI is doing wrong; the interp crashes when take is invoked after going Cave → Hall → Cave. Likely a corrupted\n  state or GC issue in the let rec loop + _ :: inv path after a round-trip through go.\n\n  This is out of scope for this repo. Options:\n\n  1. Commit/push what's done (guess timing fixes, vendor refresh, adventure resync) and file an upstream issue on ../sw-cor24-ocaml for\n  the TRAP 2. Adventure will still \"sort of work\" on the live site until upstream fixes it.\n  2. Drop text-adventure from the dropdown until upstream is fixed, so users don't hit the trap.\n  3. Simplify the local text-adventure (LOCAL_OVERRIDE) to something that doesn't trigger — e.g., remove the take command, or make take\n  one-shot per room. Risks drifting from upstream and possibly hiding other bugs.\n\n  My recommendation: option 1. The bug is real and reproducible, so an upstream issue is useful; the web UI faithfully exposes it rather\n   than papering over it. Which do you want?\n\n✻ Brewed for 1m 5s · 1 shell still running\n\n※ recap: Goal: add upstream guess demo and refresh adventure/echo-loop in the web UI. Guess now works; adventure hits an upstream TRAP 2\n   that reproduces in the CLI. Waiting on your pick: push as-is and file upstream, drop adventure, or local-patch it. (disable recaps in\n   /config)\n"},"uuid":"b3306eaa-057e-4c3d-864e-1112c0c825e1","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:19:35.893Z","permissionMode":"default","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/mike/github/sw-embed/sw-cor24-ocaml","sessionId":"e5aefad8-ffa8-4fca-baff-df2b7b63be1b","version":"2.1.116","gitBranch":"feat/wip"}
