{"parentUuid":"c6ff5843-ee3e-4cfb-82a6-50b647d14552","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"4b099836-8452-457b-ac35-63bf22a75cb1","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WtLi5pbKd3iysZbNjQQfcA","type":"tool_result","content":"Workflow CLI for keeping AI agents on track\n\nUsage: agentrail [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>\n\nCommands:\n  init            Initialize a new saga\n  setup           Bootstrap a project: create saga, CLAUDE.md, and register domain\n  add             Add a step to the saga (for maintenance mode or ad-hoc tasks)\n  status          Show current saga state\n  next            Output current step prompt and context for a fresh agent session\n  begin           Mark the current step as in-progress\n  complete        Complete current step, optionally define next step\n  plan            View or update the saga plan\n  history         Show all step summaries\n  distill         Distill trajectories into a skill document\n  run-loop        Auto-execute deterministic steps, pause at agent steps\n  abort           Mark current step as blocked\n  insert          Insert a new pending step at a chosen position, shifting later steps up\n  reorder         Move an existing pending/in-progress step to a different position\n  reopen          Reopen a completed or blocked step\n  archive         Archive current saga to .agentrail-archive/ and clear .agentrail/\n  audit           Compare git history with saga history, report gaps\n  snapshot        Save a point-in-time copy of .agentrail/ into the git object store\n  gen-agents-doc  Write AGENTS.example.md — an agent instructions template for agentrail\n  help            Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)\n\nOptions:\n      --saga <SAGA>  Path to the project directory (default: current directory) [default: .]\n  -h, --help         Print help\n  -V, --version      Print version","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"bc8f538c-5b5e-47bf-944f-6224721ef3f2","timestamp":"2026-04-21T19:15:38.824