{"parentUuid":"478766fd-c524-4787-93a9-9aadb0823412","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01BY1DBfuyRLC3yXDpWUSSqt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Jrnv9Kb7nABGLH2Qyt1sGe","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nfeat(eval): tail-call optimization in eval_expr\n\nWraps eval_expr's dispatch in a while-true trampoline. Tail-position\nrecursive calls in EK_IF, EK_LET, EK_MATCH, and user-closure EK_APP\nreassign (e, env) and fall through to the loop edge instead of\nrecursing through Pascal.\n\nBefore: a let rec loop that tail-calls itself exhausted the p-code VM\ncall stack after ~8 iterations (TRAP 2). Reproducible via e.g.\n`OCAML_STDIN=$(yes look | head -10 | ...) ./scripts/run-ocaml.sh\ntests/demo_adventure.ml`.\n\nAfter: tail recursion runs in constant Pascal-stack space. The\ndemo_adventure now accepts 100+ commands before heap exhaustion\n(TRAP 5, separate issue — no GC yet).\n\nNon-tail recursion (EK_BINOP operands, EK_APP function/arg evaluation,\nEK_MATCH scrutinee and guard expressions) continues to recurse; those\nare bounded by expression depth, not iteration count.\n\nAdds demo_tco_countdown regression: let rec count = fun n -> ...\ncount (n - 1) in count 100, which would trap without TCO.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Commit TCO + test + saga"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":421,"cache_read_input_tokens":186516,"output_tokens":585,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":421,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":585,"cache_read_input_tokens":186516,"cache_creation_input_tokens":421,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_i